<LegalPage eyebrow="Materials" heading="Materials" lede="Just as beautiful. Without the harm.">
  <p>Animal leather is a by-product of an industry built on harm. The tanning process is one of the most chemically intensive in fashion &mdash; heavy on water use, heavy on pollutants. We don&rsquo;t want any part of that. We&rsquo;d rather make something just as beautiful without it.</p>
  <p>This isn&rsquo;t a compromise. The bags look great, feel great, and last years. The only thing missing is the harm.</p>

  <h2>Apple Leather</h2>
  <p>Apple leather starts as waste. The skins and pulp left over from apple juice and food production &mdash; material that would otherwise be discarded &mdash; are dried, ground into a fine powder, and mixed with a binding agent to form a flexible, durable sheet. It&rsquo;s then finished to achieve the texture, weight, and surface feel we&rsquo;re after.</p>
  <p>Ours is sourced from Italy, where the apple industry produces a consistent, high-quality supply year-round. The result has structure, softness, and a clean natural scent.</p>

  <h2>Other Plant Leathers</h2>
  <p>We work with leathers made from other plant sources too &mdash; cactus, pineapple, and other fruit and vegetable by-products developed through a similar process. Food industry waste, transformed into something durable and well-finished.</p>

  <h2>Microfibre Leather</h2>
  <p>Microfibre is one of those materials that doesn&rsquo;t get enough credit. It&rsquo;s exceptionally soft against the hand, consistent in finish, and remarkably durable over time. We use it in select styles where we want a lighter weight and a refined, smooth surface. It performs quietly and reliably &mdash; exactly what we look for.</p>

  <h2>Synthetic Vegan Leather</h2>
  <p>Not all synthetic materials are created equal. The ones we use are engineered for performance &mdash; and in our testing, several have matched or outperformed conventional leather on durability, scratch resistance, and finish consistency. We choose materials on merit. If a synthetic vegan leather holds up better for a particular bag, that&rsquo;s what we use.</p>

  <h2>Every detail, considered</h2>
  <p>The material is only part of it. Every Mir Kash bag is handcrafted &mdash; and the quality shows in how it feels to use. Stitching, zips, clasps, hardware &mdash; each detail is considered and tested until it&rsquo;s exactly right. We believe a bag should be a pleasure to use, not just to look at.</p>
</LegalPage>
